idn\'t want to be called crippled, just\nlike I didn\'t want to be called stupid.',-1),(89850,42,120620,120665,'01:23:45.854','01:23:47.731','Happy New Year, Gump.',-1),(89851,42,120780,120814,'01:23:52.528','01:23:53.946','The US Ping-Pong team',-1),(89852,42,120815,120872,'01:23:53.987','01:23:56.341','met with President Nixon today\nat an Oval Office ceremony...',-1),(89853,42,120872,120938,'01:23:56.365','01:23:59.117','And wouldn\'t you know it?\nA few months later,',-1),(89854,42,120940,121035,'01:23:59.201','01:24:03.163','they invited me and the Ping-Pong team\nto visit the White House.',-1),(89855,42,121037,121091,'01:24:03.247','01:24:05.499','So, I went, again.',-1),(89856,42,121111,121195,'01:24:06.333','01:24:09.795','And I met the President\nof the United States, again.',-1),(89857,42,121213,121284,'01:24:10.546','01:24:13.507','Only, this time, they didn\'t get us rooms\nin a real fancy hotel.',-1),(89858,42,121286,121367,'01:24:13.590','01:24:16.969','So, are you enjoying yourself\nin our nation\'s capital, young man?',-1),(89859,42,121369,121441,'01:24:17.052','01:24:20.055','- Yes, sir.\n- Well, where are you staying?',-1),(89860,42,121443,121506,'01:24:20.138','01:24:22.766','- It\'s called the Hotel Ebbott.\n- Oh, no, no, no, no.',-1),(89861,42,121508,121583,'01:24:22.849','01:24:25.978','I know of a much nicer hotel.\nIt\'s brand-new, very modern.',-1),(89862,42,121585,121633,'01:24:26.061','01:24:28.063','I\'ll have my people\ntake care of it for you.',-1),(89863,42,121648,121675,'01:24:28.689','01:24:29.815','Security, Frank Wills.',-1),(89864,42,121677,121763,'01:24:29.898','01:24:33.485','Yeah, sir, you might want\nto send a maintenance man',-1),(89865,42,121765,121830,'01:24:33.569','01:24:36.280','over to that office across the way.',-1),(89866,42,121831,121900,'01:24:36.321','01:24:39.201','The lights are off, and they must be\nlooking for a fuse box or something,',-1),(89867,42,121902,121967,'01:24:39.283','01:24:41.994','\'cause them flashlights,\nthey\'re keeping me awake.',-1),(89868,42,121969,122008,'01:24:42.077','01:24:43.704','Okay, sir. I\'ll check it out.',-1),(89869,42,122010,122051,'01:24:43.787','01:24:45.497','- Thank you.\n- No problem.',-1),(89870,42,122053,122099,'01:24:45.581','01:24:47.499','- Good night.\n- Good night.',-1),(89871,42,122187,122316,'01:24:51.128','01:24:56.508','Therefore, I shall resign the presidency\neffective at noon tomorrow.',-1),(89872,42,122318,122367,'01:24:56.592','01:24:58.635','Vice President Ford',-1),(89873,42,122369,122477,'01:24:58.719','01:25:03.223','will be sworn in as president\nat that hour in this office.',-1),(89874,42,122510,122625,'01:25:04.600','01:25:09.396','As I recall the high hopes for America\nwith which we began this second term...',-1),(89875,42,122751,122788,'01:25:14.651','01:25:16.194','Sergeant Gump.',-1),(89876,42,122800,122853,'01:25:16.695','01:25:18.905','- Yes, sir!\n- As you were.',-1),(89877,42,122855,122930,'01:25:18.989','01:25:22.117','I have your discharge papers.\nYour service is up, son.',-1),(89878,42,123012,123078,'01:25:25.537','01:25:28.290','Does this mean\nI can\'t play Ping-Pong no more?',-1),(89879,42,123080,123128,'01:25:28.373','01:25:30.334','For the Army it does.',-1),(89880,42,123191,123308,'01:25:32.961','01:25:37.841','And just like that, my service\nin the United States Army was over.',-1),(89881,42,123435,123478,'01:25:43.138','01:25:44.931','So, I went home.',-1),(89882,42,123993,124075,'01:26:06.411','01:26:09.831','- I\'m home, Mama.\n- I know, I know.',-1),(89883,42,124114,124153,'01:26:11.458','01:26:13.061','- Louise, he\'s here.\n- Now, when I got home,',-1),(89884,42,124154,124251,'01:26:13.085','01:26:17.130','I had no idea,\nbut Mama had had all sorts of visitors.',-1),(89885,42,124254,124310,'01:26:17.255','01:26:19.591','We\'ve had all sorts of visitors, Forrest.',-1),(89886,42,124311,124386,'01:26:19.633','01:26:22.761','Everybody wants you\nto use their Ping-Pong stuff.',-1),(89887,42,124387,124478,'01:26:22.803','01:26:26.598','One man even left a check for $25,000',-1),(89888,42,124480,124563,'01:26:26.682','01:26:30.143','if you\'d be agreeable to saying\nyou liked using their paddle.',-1),(89889,42,124566,124630,'01:26:30.268','01:26:32.938','Oh, but, Mama,\nI only like using my own paddle.',-1),(89890,42,124632,124680,'01:26:33.021','01:26:35.023','- Hi, Miss Louise.\n- Hey, Forrest.',-1),(89891,42,124682,124752,'01:26:35.107','01:26:38.026','I know that. I know that.',-1),(89892,42,124754,124818,'01:26:38.110','01:26:40.779','But it\'s $25,000, Forrest.',-1),(89893,42,124820,124933,'01:26:40.862','01:26:45.575','I thought maybe you could hold it\nfor a while, see if it grows on you.',-1),(89894,42,124934,124987,'01:26:45.617','01:26:47.804','- Oh, you look good, Forrest.\n- That Mama, she sure was right.',-1),(89895,42,124987,125047,'01:26:47.828','01:26:50.330','- You look real good.\n- It\'s funny how things work out.',-1),(89896,42,125050,125127,'01:26:50.455','01:26:53.625','I didn\'t stay home for long,\nbecause I\'d made a promise to Bubba,',-1),(89897,42,125128,125183,'01:26:53.667','01:26:55.961','and I always try to keep my promise.',-1),(89898,42,125184,125221,'01:26:56.002','01:26:57.546','So, I went on down to Bayou La Batre',-1),(89899,42,125223,125313,'01:26:57.629','01:27:01.383','to meet Bubba\'s family\nand make their introduction.',-1),(89900,42,125315,125403,'01:27:01.466','01:27:05.137','Are you crazy, or just plain stupid?',-1),(89901,42,125420,125475,'01:27:05.846','01:27:08.140','Stupid is as stupid does, Mrs. Blue.',-1),(89902,42,125476,125509,'01:27:08.181','01:27:09.558','I guess.',-1),(89903,42,125533,125619,'01:27:10.559','01:27:14.146','And, of course,\nI paid my respect to Bubba himself',-1),(89904,42,125667,125728,'01:27:16.148','01:27:18.692','Hey, Bubba, it\'s me, Forrest Gump.',-1),(89905,42,125803,125900,'01:27:21.820','01:27:25.866','I remember everything you said,\nand I got it all figured out.',-1),(89906,42,125967,126131,'01:27:28.660','01:27:35.459','I\'m taking the $24,562\nand 47 cents that I got...',-1),(89907,42,126157,126244,'01:27:36.543','01:27:40.172','Or, that\'s left after a new hair cut\nand a new suit,',-1),(89908,42,126245,126292,'01:27:40.213','01:27:42.174','and I took Mama out\nto a real fancy dinner,',-1),(89909,42,126294,126372,'01:27:42.257','01:27:45.510','and I bought a bus ticket\nand three Dr. Peppers.',-1),(89910,42,126385,126428,'01:27:46.052','01:27:47.846','Tell me something.',-1),(89911,42,126453,126504,'01:27:48.889','01:27:51.016','Are you stupid or something?',-1),(89912,42,126506,126556,'01:27:51.099','01:27:53.185','Stupid is as stupid does, sir.',-1),(89913,42,126557,126628,'01:27:53.226','01:27:56.188','Well, that\'s what\'s left after me saying,',-1),(89914,42,126650,126702,'01:27:57.105','01:27:59.265','\"When I was in China\non the All-America Ping-Pong team,',-1),(89915,42,126704,126796,'01:27:59.357','01:28:03.195','\"I just loved playing Ping-Pong with\nmy Flex-O-Light Ping-Pong paddle,\"',-1),(89916,42,126797,126829,'01:28:03.236','01:28:04.547','which everybody knows isn\'t true,',-1),(89917,42,126829,126864,'01:28:04.571','01:28:06.007','but Mama says it\'s just a little white lie',-1),(89918,42,126864,126916,'01:28:06.031','01:28:08.200','so it wouldn\'t hurt nobody.',-1),(89919,42,126950,127092,'01:28:09.618','01:28:15.540','So, anyway, I\'m putting all that on gas,\nropes and new nets',-1),(89920,42,127110,127153,'01:28:16.291','01:28:18.043','and a brand-new shrimping boat.',-1),(89921,42,127673,127751,'01:28:39.731','01:28:42.984','Now, Bubba had told me everything\nhe knew about shrimping,',-1),(89922,42,127753,127809,'01:28:43.068','01:28:45.403','but you know what I found out?',-1),(89923,42,127849,127905,'01:28:47.072','01:28:49.407','Shrimping is tough.',-1),(89924,42,127958,128002,'01:28:51.618','01:28:53.453','I only caught five.',-1),(89925,42,128005,128085,'01:28:53.578','01:28:56.915','A couple more,\nyou could have yourself a cocktail.',-1),(89926,42,128166,128209,'01:29:00.252','01:29:02.063','Hey, you ever think\nabout naming this old boat?',-1),(89927,42,128210,128274,'01:29:02.087','01:29:04.756','It\'s bad luck\nto have a boat without a name.',-1),(89928,42,128331,128447,'01:29:07.133','01:29:11.972','I\'d never named a boat before,\nbut there was only one I could think of,',-1),(89929,42,128475,128552,'01:29:13.139','01:29:16.351','the most beautiful name\nin the wide world.',-1),(89930,42,129056,129124,'01:29:37.372','01:29:40.208','Now, I hadn\'t heard from Jenny\nin a long while,',-1),(89931,42,129127,129188,'01:29:40.292','01:29:42.836','but I thought about her a lot,',-1),(89932,42,129191,129274,'01:29:42.961','01:29:46.423','and I hoped that whatever\nshe was doing made her happy.',-1),(89933,42,131824,131885,'01:31:32.696','01:31:35.240','I thought about Jenny all the time.',-1),(89934,42,132477,132505,'01:31:59.889','01:32:01.057','Hey!',-1),(89935,42,133077,133190,'01:32:24.914','01:32:29.586','Lieutenant Dan,\nwhat are you doing here?',-1),(89936,42,133192,133287,'01:32:29.669','01:32:33.631','Well, thought I\'d try out my sea legs.',-1),(89937,42,133288,133379,'01:32:33.673','01:32:37.469','But you ain\'t got no legs,\nLieutenant Dan.',-1),(89938,42,133380,133435,'01:32:37.510','01:32:39.804','Yes, I know that.',-1),(89939,42,133443,133492,'01:32:40.138','01:32:42.182','You wrote me a letter, you idiot.',-1),(89940,42,133495,133604,'01:32:42.307','01:32:46.853','Well, well. Captain Forrest Gump.\nI had to see this for myself.',-1),(89941,42,133643,133808,'01:32:48.480','01:32:55.361','And I told you if you were ever\na shrimp boat captain',-1),(89942,42,133811,133874,'01:32:55.487','01:32:58.114','that I\'d be your first mate.\nWell, here I am.',-1),(89943,42,133875,133951,'01:32:58.156','01:33:01.326','- I am a man of my word.\n- Okay.',-1),(89944,42,133952,134048,'01:33:01.367','01:33:05.371','Yeah, but don\'t you be thinking that\nI\'m going to be calling you \"sir.\"',-1),(89945,42,134051,134083,'01:33:05.497','01:33:06.831','No, sir.',-1),(89946,42,134297,134352,'01:33:15.715','01:33:18.009','That\'s my boat.',-1),(89947,42,134414,134545,'01:33:20.595','01:33:26.059','I have a feeling if we head due east,\nwe\'ll find some shrimp,',-1),(89948,42,134548,134586,'01:33:26.184','01:33:27.769','so take a left.',-1),(89949,42,134620,134690,'01:33:29.187','01:33:32.107','- Take a left!\n- Which way?',-1),(89950,42,134692,134756,'01:33:32.190','01:33:34.859','Over there! They\'re over there!',-1),(89951,42,134772,134864,'01:33:35.527','01:33:39.364','- Get on the wheel and take a left!\n- Okay.',-1),(89952,42,134893,134992,'01:33:40.573','01:33:44.702','Gump, what are you doing?\nTake a left! Left!',-1),(89953,42,135049,135136,'01:33:47.080','01:33:50.708','That\'s where we\'re going\nto find those shrimp, my boy!',-1),(89954,42,135175,135213,'01:33:52.293','01:33:53.878','That\'s where we\'ll find them.',-1),(89955,42,135517,135616,'01:34:06.558','01:34:10.687','- Still no shrimp, Lieutenant Dan.\n- Okay, so I was wrong.',-1),(89956,42,135633,135710,'01:34:11.396','01:34:14.607','How are we going to find them?',-1),(89957,42,135713,135773,'01:34:14.732','01:34:17.235','Well, maybe you should\njust pray for shrimp.',-1),(89958,42,135932,135996,'01:34:23.867','01:34:26.536','So, I went to church every Sunday.',-1),(89959,42,136026,136074,'01:34:27.787','01:34:29.789','Sometimes Lieutenant Dan came, too,',-1),(89960,42,136077,136150,'01:34:29.914','01:34:32.917','though I think\nhe left the praying up to me.',-1),(89961,42,136521,136626,'01:34:48.391','01:34:52.770','- No shrimp.\n- Where the hell\'s this God of yours?',-1),(89962,42,136646,136783,'01:34:53.605','01:34:59.319','It\'s funny Lieutenant Dan said that,\n\'cause right then, God showed up.',-1),(89963,42,137188,137304,'01:35:16.169','01:35:21.007','- You\'ll never sink this boat!\n- Now, me, I was scared,',-1),(89964,42,137307,137380,'01:35:21.132','01:35:24.177','but Lieutenant Dan, he was mad.',-1),(89965,42,137383,137415,'01:35:24.302','01:35:25.637','Come on!',-1),(89966,42,137490,137615,'01:35:28.765','01:35:33.978','You call this a storm?\nCome on, you son of a bitch!',-1),(89967,42,137666,137771,'01:35:36.105','01:35:40.485','It\'s time for a showdown! You and me!',-1),(89968,42,137774,137867,'01:35:40.610','01:35:44.489','I\'m right here! Come and get me!',-1),(89969,42,137910,138003,'01:35:46.282','01:35:50.161','You\'ll never sink this boat!',-1),(89970,42,138052,138104,'01:35:52.205','01:35:54.374','Hurricane Carmen\ncame through here yesterday,',-1),(89971,42,138107,138169,'01:35:54.499','01:35:57.043','destroying nearly everything in its path.',-1),(89972,42,138172,138232,'01:35:57.168','01:35:59.671','And as in other towns\nup and down the coast,',-1),(89973,42,138236,138293,'01:35:59.837','01:36:02.215','Bayou La Batre\'s\nentire shrimping industry',-1),(89974,42,138295,138388,'01:36:02.298','01:36:06.177','has fallen victim to Carmen\nand has been left in utter ruin.',-1),(89975,42,138391,138467,'01:36:06.302','01:36:09.472','Speaking with local officials,\nthis reporter has learned,',-1),(89976,42,138468,138551,'01:36:09.514','01:36:12.976','in fact, only one shrimping boat\nactually survived the storm.',-1),(89977,42,138560,138623,'01:36:13.351','01:36:15.979','Louise. Louise, there\'s Forrest.',-1),(89978,42,138640,138688,'01:36:16.688','01:36:18.690','After that, shrimping was easy.',-1),(89979,42,138824,138900,'01:36:24.362','01:36:27.532','Since people still needed\nthem shrimps for shrimp cocktails',-1),(89980,42,138901,139000,'01:36:27.573','01:36:31.703','and barbecues and all,\nand we were the only boat left standing,',-1),(89981,42,139004,139083,'01:36:31.869','01:36:35.164','Bubba-Gump Shrimp\'s what they got.',-1),(89982,42,139084,139196,'01:36:35.206','01:36:39.836','We got a whole bunch of boats,\n12 Jennys,',-1),(89983,42,139197,139281,'01:36:39.877','01:36:43.381','a big old warehouse. We even have\nhats that say \"Bubba-Gump\" on them.',-1),(89984,42,139289,139368,'01:36:43.715','01:36:47.010','Bubba-Gump Shrimp.\nIt\'s a household name.',-1),(89985,42,139373,139414,'01:36:47.218','01:36:48.928','Hold on there, boy.',-1),(89986,42,139417,139526,'01:36:49.053','01:36:53.599','Are you telling me you\'re the owner of\nthe Bubba-Gump Shrimp Corporation?',-1),(89987,42,139529,139601,'01:36:53.725','01:36:56.728','Yes, sir. We got more money\nthan Davy Crockett.',-1),(89988,42,139640,139737,'01:36:58.354','01:37:02.400','Boy, I heard some whoppers in my time,\nbut that tops them all.',-1),(89989,42,139802,139869,'01:37:05.111','01:37:07.905','We was sitting next to a millionaire.',-1),(89990,42,139953,140064,'01:37:11.409','01:37:16.039','Well, I thought it was a very lovely story,',-1),(89991,42,140074,140186,'01:37:16.456','01:37:21.085','and you tell it so well,\nwith such enthusiasm.',-1),(89992,42,140227,140291,'01:37:22.795','01:37:25.465','Would you like to see\nwhat Lieutenant Dan looks like?',-1),(89993,42,140294,140330,'01:37:25.590','01:37:27.091','Well, yes, I would.',-1),(89994,42,140455,140504,'01:37:32.305','01:37:34.349','That\'s him right there.',-1),(89995,42,140555,140609,'01:37:36.476','01:37:38.728','And let me tell you something\nabout Lieutenant Dan...',-1),(89996,42,140637,140662,'01:37:39.896','01:37:40.938','Forrest,',-1),(89997,42,140795,140862,'01:37:46.486','01:37:49.280','I never thanked you for saving my life.',-1),(89998,42,141487,141638,'01:38:15.306','01:38:21.604','He never actually said so,\nbut I think he made his peace with God.',-1),(89999,42,141822,141875,'01:38:29.278','01:38:31.489','For the second time in 17 days,',-1),(90000,42,141878,141961,'01:38:31.614','01:38:35.076','President Ford escaped\npossible assassination today.',-1),(90001,42,141963,141995,'01:38:35.159','01:38:36.494','Base to Jenny 1.',-1),(90002,42,141996,142080,'01:38:36.536','01:38:40.039','- Base to Jenny 1.\n- Jenny 1. Go, Margo.',-1),(90003,42,142082,142119,'01:38:40.123','01:38:41.666','Forrest has a phone call.',-1),(90004,42,142120,142181,'01:38:41.707','01:38:44.210','Yeah, well, you\'ll have to tell them\nto call him back.',-1),(90005,42,142183,142264,'01:38:44.293','01:38:47.672','- He is indisposed at the moment.\n- His mama\'s sick.',-1),(90006,42,142760,142817,'01:39:08.359','01:39:10.736','- Where\'s Mama?\n- She\'s upstairs.',-1),(90007,42,142885,142932,'01:39:13.573','01:39:15.533','Hi, Forrest.',-1),(90008,42,142955,143016,'01:39:16.492','01:39:19.036','- I\'ll see you tomorrow.\n- All right.',-1),(90009,42,143177,143253,'01:39:25.710','01:39:28.880','We sure got you straightened out,\ndidn\'t we, boy?',-1),(90010,42,143525,143620,'01:39:40.224','01:39:44.187','- What\'s the matter, Mama?\n- I\'m dying, Forrest.',-1),(90011,42,143700,143757,'01:39:47.523','01:39:49.901','Come on in, sit down over here.',-1),(90012,42,144101,144186,'01:40:04.248','01:40:07.752','- Why are you dying, Mama?\n- It\'s my time.',-1),(90013,42,144210,144255,'01:40:08.753','01:40:10.630','It\'s just my time.',-1),(90014,42,144290,144390,'01:40:12.089','01:40:16.260','Now, don\'t you be afraid, sweetheart.',-1),(90015,42,144429,144486,'01:40:17.887','01:40:20.264','Death is just a part of life,',-1),(90016,42,144510,144573,'01:40:21.265','01:40:23.893','something we\'re all destined to do.',-1),(90017,42,144617,144722,'01:40:25.728','01:40:30.107','I didn\'t know it,\nbut I was destined to be your mama.',-1),(90018,42,144742,144828,'01:40:30.942','01:40:34.529','- I did the best I could.\n- You did good, Mama.',-1),(90019,42,144847,144971,'01:40:35.321','01:40:40.493','Well, I happen to believe\nyou make your own destiny.',-1),(90020,42,145007,145085,'01:40:41.994','01:40:45.248','You have to do the best\nwith what God gave you.',-1),(90021,42,145179,145230,'01:40:49.126','01:40:51.254','What\'s my destiny, Mama?',-1),(90022,42,145282,145359,'01:40:53.422','01:40:56.634','You\'re going to have\nto figure that out for yourself.',-1),(90023,42,145390,145462,'01:40:57.927','01:41:00.930','Life is a box of chocolates, Forrest.',-1),(90024,42,145463,145515,'01:41:00.972','01:41:03.140','You never know\nwhat you\'re going to get.',-1),(90025,42,145518,145623,'01:41:03.266','01:41:07.645','Mama always had a way of explaining\nthings so I could understand them.',-1),(90026,42,145625,145678,'01:41:07.728','01:41:09.939','I will miss you, Forrest.',-1),(90027,42,145722,145819,'01:41:11.774','01:41:15.820','She had got the cancer\nand died on a Tuesday.',-1),(90028,42,145855,145935,'01:41:17.321','01:41:20.658','I bought her a new hat\nwith little flowers on it.',-1),(90029,42,146008,146087,'01:41:23.703','01:41:26.998','And that\'s all I have to say about that.',-1),(90030,42,146252,146308,'01:41:33.838','01:41:36.173','Didn\'t you say you were waiting\nfor the number seven bus?',-1),(90031,42,146309,146376,'01:41:36.215','01:41:39.010','There\'ll be another one along shortly.',-1),(90032,42,146468,146555,'01:41:42.847','01:41:46.475','Now, because I had been a football star,\nand a war hero,',-1),(90033,42,146556,146631,'01:41:46.517','01:41:49.645','and a national celebrity,\nand a shrimping boat captain,',-1),(90034,42,146643,146720,'01:41:50.146','01:41:53.357','and a college graduate,\nthe city fathers of Greenbow, Alabama',-1),(90035,42,146723,146800,'01:41:53.482','01:41:56.694','decided to get together\nand offered me a fine job.',-1),(90036,42,146833,146921,'01:41:58.070','01:42:01.741','So, I never went back to work\nfor Lieutenant Dan,',-1),(90037,42,146924,146989,'01:42:01.866','01:42:04.577','though he did take care\nof my Bubba-Gump money.',-1),(90038,42,146992,147103,'01:42:04.702','01:42:09.332','He got me invested\nin some kind of fruit company.',-1),(90039,42,147104,147144,'01:42:09.373','01:42:11.013','And so then, I got a call from him saying',-1),(90040,42,147145,147229,'01:42:11.042','01:42:14.545','we don\'t have to worry about money\nno more, and I said,',-1),(90041,42,147230,147285,'01:42:14.587','01:42:16.881','\"That\'s good. One less thing.\"',-1),(90042,42,147358,147439,'01:42:19.925','01:42:23.304','Now, Mama said there\'s only\nso much fortune a man really needs,',-1),(90043,42,147469,147538,'01:42:24.555','01:42:27.433','and the rest is just for showing off',-1),(90044,42,147540,147633,'01:42:27.516','01:42:31.395','So, I gave a whole bunch of it\nto the Foursquare gospel church,',-1),(90045,42,147697,147805,'01:42:34.065','01:42:38.569','and I gave a whole bunch to the\nBayou La Batre fishing hospital.',-1),(90046,42,147861,147970,'01:42:40.905','01:42:45.451','And even though Bubba was dead\nand Lieutenant Dan said I was nuts,',-1),(90047,42,147973,148036,'01:42:45.576','01:42:48.204','I gave Bubba\'s mama Bubba\'s share.',-1),(90048,42,148137,148179,'01:42:52.416','01:42:54.126','You know what?',-1),(90049,42,148209,148282,'01:42:55.378','01:42:58.422','She didn\'t have to work\nin nobody\'s kitchen no more.',-1),(90050,42,148283,148322,'01:42:58.464','01:43:00.091','That smells wonderful.',-1),(90051,42,148342,148437,'01:43:00.925','01:43:04.887','And \'cause I was a gazillionaire\nand I liked doing it so much,',-1),(90052,42,148438,148494,'01:43:04.929','01:43:07.264','I cut that grass for free.',-1),(90053,42,148585,148654,'01:43:11.060','01:43:13.938','But at night time\nwhen there was nothing to do',-1),(90054,42,148656,148713,'01:43:14.021','01:43:16.399','and the house was all empty,',-1),(90055,42,148737,148794,'01:43:17.400','01:43:19.777','I\'d always think of Jenny.',-1),(90056,42,150323,150399,'01:44:23.466','01:44:26.635','And then, she was there.',-1),(90057,42,151191,151267,'01:44:59.627','01:45:02.797','- Hello, Forrest.\n- Hello, Jenny.',-1),(90058,42,151544,151607,'01:45:14.350','01:45:16.977','Jenny came back and stayed with me.',-1),(90059,42,151645,151733,'01:45:18.562','01:45:22.233','Maybe it was because\nshe had nowhere else to go,',-1),(90060,42,151736,151825,'01:45:22.358','