ociate publisher.',-1),(103746,45,13980,14069,'00:09:42.540','00:09:46.210','We had both ordered sandwiches...',-1),(103747,45,14073,14173,'00:09:46.378','00:09:50.547','...and he got my tomato on wheat,\nwhich he\'s allergic to.',-1),(103748,45,14177,14284,'00:09:50.715','00:09:55.177','And I got his tomato on white.\nAmazing, isn\'t it?',-1),(103749,45,14288,14408,'00:09:55.345','00:10:00.349','You make a million decisions,\nand a sandwich changes your life.',-1),(103750,45,14412,14478,'00:10:00.517','00:10:03.269','Destiny takes a hand.',-1),(103751,45,14482,14619,'00:10:03.436','00:10:09.149','We invented destiny, because we\ndon\'t want things to be accidental.',-1),(103752,45,14623,14746,'00:10:09.317','00:10:14.446','Then why did you order the same\nsandwich except for the bread?',-1),(103753,45,14750,14917,'00:10:14.614','00:10:21.578','How many people like tomato\nwithout something else, like tuna?',-1),(103754,45,14922,15015,'00:10:21.788','00:10:25.666','It wasn\'t a sign.\nIt was a coincidence.',-1),(103755,45,15020,15123,'00:10:25.834','00:10:30.129','I was in Atlantic City,\nwhere Cliff was a waiter.',-1),(103756,45,15127,15234,'00:10:30.297','00:10:34.758','He wasn\'t supposed to work\nthat night. What if he hadn\'t?',-1),(103757,45,15238,15426,'00:10:34.926','00:10:42.766','He asked me to take a midnight walk.\nI told you this a million times.',-1),(103758,45,15430,15627,'00:10:42.934','00:10:51.150','He held my hand. I looked down\nand couldn\'t tell our fingers apart.',-1),(103759,45,15631,15741,'00:10:51.318','00:10:55.904','- And I knew.\n- What?',-1),(103760,45,15782,15917,'00:10:57.615','00:11:03.245','- What?\n- It was magic.',-1),(103761,45,15931,15963,'00:11:03.830','00:11:05.164','Magic.',-1),(103762,45,15967,16139,'00:11:05.332','00:11:12.463','I knew we\'d be together forever.\nJust like you and Walter.',-1),(103763,45,16143,16248,'00:11:12.630','00:11:17.009','Walter. It\'s quite a formal name.',-1),(103764,45,16266,16414,'00:11:17.761',