be, Anesthesia-',-1),(112983,39,19122,19166,'00:13:16.763','00:13:18.598','They\'re inbound!',-1),(112984,39,19286,19380,'00:13:23.603','00:13:27.524','Rose DeWitt Bukater died on the\nTitanic when she was 17, right?',-1),(112985,39,19402,19470,'00:13:28.442','00:13:31.278','BROCK: That\'s right.\nBODINE: If she had lived, she\'d be over 100 by now.',-1),(112986,39,19478,19530,'00:13:31.611','00:13:33.780','101 next month.',-1),(112987,39,19538,19606,'00:13:34.114','00:13:36.950','Okay, so she\'s a very\nold goddamn liar.',-1),(112988,39,19612,19664,'00:13:37.200','00:13:39.369','Look, I\'ve already done the\nbackground on this woman...',-1),(112989,39,19670,19716,'00:13:39.619','00:13:41.538','...all the way\nback to the 20s,',-1),(112990,39,19717,19762,'00:13:41.580','00:13:43.457','when she was working\nas an actress.',-1),(112991,39,19770,19839,'00:13:43.790','00:13:46.626','An actress. There\'s your\nfirst clue, Sherlock.',-1),(112992,39,19847,19901,'00:13:46.960','00:13:49.212','Her name was\nRose Dawson back then.',-1),(112993,39,19902,19950,'00:13:49.254','00:13:51.256','Then she marries\nthis guy named Calvert.',-1),(112994,39,19955,20035,'00:13:51.465','00:13:54.801','They move to Cedar Rapids and she\npunches out a couple of kids.',-1),(112995,39,20043,20119,'00:13:55.135','00:13:58.305','Now Calvert\'s dead and, from what\nI hear, Cedar Rapids is dead.',-1),(112996,39,20125,20181,'00:13:58.555','00:14:00.891','And everybody who knows about the\ndiamond is supposed to be dead...',-1),(112997,39,20186,20234,'00:14:01.099','00:14:03.101','...or on this boat,\nbut she knows.',-1),(112998,39,20555,20617,'00:14:16.490','00:14:19.076','Doesn\'t exactly\ntravel light, does she?',-1),(112999,39,20626,20651,'00:14:19.451','00:14:20.494','Hurry up, give him a hand.',-1),(113000,39,20669,20757,'00:14:21.244','00:14:24.915','Mrs. Calvert, I\'m Brock Lovett.\nWelcorne to the Keldysh.',-1),(113001,39,20812,20856,'00:14:27.167','00:14:29.002','Okay, let\'s get\nher inside there.',-1),(113002,39,20868,20892,'00:14:29.503','00:14:30.504','Hi, Miss Calvert.',-1),(113003,39,20908,20946,'00:14:31.171','00:14:32.756','- Hi.\n- Welcome to the Keldysh.',-1),(113004,39,20964,20996,'00:14:33.507','00:14:34.841','Thanks.',-1),(113005,39,21036,21060,'00:14:36.510','00:14:37.511','PILOT: Hey!',-1),(113006,39,21194,21241,'00:14:43.100','00:14:45.060','(KNOCKING)',-1),(113007,39,21256,21290,'00:14:45.685','00:14:47.104','Are your staterooms all right?',-1),(113008,39,21292,21316,'00:14:47.187','00:14:48.188','Oh, yes.',-1),(113009,39,21319,21344,'00:14:48.313','00:14:49.356','Very nice.',-1),(113010,39,21350,21398,'00:14:49.606','00:14:51.608','Have you met my\ngranddaughter, Lizzy?',-1),(113011,39,21401,21439,'00:14:51.733','00:14:53.318','She takes care of me.',-1),(113012,39,21462,21511,'00:14:54.277','00:14:56.321','We met just a few minutes ago.',-1),(113013,39,21514,21543,'00:14:56.446','00:14:57.656','Remember, Nana?\nUp on deck?',-1),(113014,39,21550,21576,'00:14:57.948','00:14:59.032','Oh, yes.',-1),(113015,39,21578,21604,'00:14:59.116','00:15:00.200','(BODINE TUTS)',-1),(113016,39,21607,21643,'00:15:00.325','00:15:01.827','There. That\'s nice.',-1),(113017,39,21654,21708,'00:15:02.285','00:15:04.538','Have to have my\npictures when I travel.',-1),(113018,39,21712,21736,'00:15:04.704','00:15:05.705','Can I get you anything?',-1),(113019,39,21738,21768,'00:15:05.789','00:15:07.040','Is there anything you\'d like?',-1),(113020,39,21807,21835,'00:15:08.625','00:15:09.793','Yes.',-1),(113021,39,21847,21903,'00:15:10.293','00:15:12.629','I would like to see my drawing.',-1),(113022,39,22235,22305,'00:15:26.476','00:15:29.396','BROCK: Louis XVI wore\na fabulous stone that was...',-1),(113023,39,22310,22348,'00:15:29.604','00:15:31.189','...called the Blue Diamond\nof the Crown...',-1),(113024,39,22355,22419,'00:15:31.481','00:15:34.151','...which disappeared\nin 1792...',-1),(113025,39,22425,22513,'00:15:34.401','00:15:38.071','...about the same time old Louis\nlost everything from the neck up.',-1),(113026,39,22527,22611,'00:15:38.655','00:15:42.159','The theory goes that the crown\ndiamond was chopped, too.',-1),(113027,39,22631,22671,'00:15:42.993','00:15:44.661','Recut into a heart-like shape\nthat became known as...',-1),(113028,39,22688,22724,'00:15:45.370','00:15:46.872','...the Heart of the Ocean.',-1),(113029,39,22729,22793,'00:15:47.080','00:15:49.749','Today it would be worth\nmore than the Hope diamond.',-1),(113030,39,22800,22852,'00:15:50.000','00:15:52.169','(SCOFFS) It was a dreadful,\nheavy thing.',-1),(113031,39,22860,22908,'00:15:52.502','00:15:54.504','I only wore it this once.',-1),(113032,39,22926,22970,'00:15:55.255','00:15:57.090','You actually think\nthis is you, Nana?',-1),(113033,39,22976,23021,'00:15:57.340','00:15:59.217','It is me, dear.',-1),(113034,39,23027,23069,'00:15:59.468','00:16:01.219','Wasn\'t I a dish?',-1),(113035,39,23095,23182,'00:16:02.304','00:16:05.932','(LAUGHS) I tracked it down\nthrough insurance records.',-1),(113036,39,23188,23278,'00:16:06.183','00:16:09.936','An old claim that was settled\nunder terms of absolute secrecy.',-1),(113037,39,23304,23368,'00:16:11.021','00:16:13.690','Can you tell me who the\nclaimant was, Rose?',-1),(113038,39,23376,23438,'00:16:14.024','00:16:16.610','I should imagine someone\nnamed Hockley.',-1),(113039,39,23448,23487,'00:16:17.027','00:16:18.653','BROCK: Nathan Hockley,\nthat\'s right.',-1),(113040,39,23502,23546,'00:16:19.279','00:16:21.114','Pittsburgh steel tycoon.',-1),(113041,39,23552,23609,'00:16:21.364','00:16:23.742','The claim was for a\ndiamond necklace his son...',-1),(113042,39,23611,23646,'00:16:23.825','00:16:25.285','...Caledon,\nbought his fiance.',-1),(113043,39,23656,23680,'00:16:25.702','00:16:26.703','You.',-1),(113044,39,23690,23744,'00:16:27.120','00:16:29.372','A week before he\nsailed on Titanic.',-1),(113045,39,23768,23825,'00:16:30.373','00:16:32.709','And it was filed right\nafter the sinking.',-1),(113046,39,23845,23919,'00:16:33.543','00:16:36.630','So the diamond had to have\ngone down with the ship.',-1),(113047,39,23953,23981,'00:16:38.048','00:16:39.216','You see the date?',-1),(113048,39,24017,24065,'00:16:40.717','00:16:42.719','April 14, 1912.',-1),(113049,39,24073,24141,'00:16:43.053','00:16:45.889','Which means if your grandmother\nis who she says she is...',-1),(113050,39,24147,24211,'00:16:46.139','00:16:48.808','...she was wearing the diamond\nthe day the Titanic sank.',-1),(113051,39,24217,24292,'00:16:49.059','00:16:52.187','And that makes you\nmy new best friend.',-1),(113052,39,24313,24364,'00:16:53.063','00:16:55.190','<i>These are some of the things we\nrecovered from your stateroom.</i>',-1),(113053,39,24449,24493,'00:16:58.735','00:17:00.570','This was mine.',-1),(113054,39,24494,24519,'00:17:00.612','00:17:01.655','(ROSE GASPS)',-1),(113055,39,24521,24573,'00:17:01.738','00:17:03.907','How extraordinary.',-1),(113056,39,24589,24671,'00:17:04.574','00:17:07.994','And it looks the same as it\ndid the last time I saw it.',-1),(113057,39,24709,24740,'00:17:09.579','00:17:10.872','(SIGHS)',-1),(113058,39,24751,24775,'00:17:11.331','00:17:12.332','Hmm.',-1),(113059,39,24810,24870,'00:17:13.750','00:17:16.253','The reflection has\nchanged a bit.',-1),(113060,39,25266,25330,'00:17:32.769','00:17:35.438','Are you ready to go\nback to Titanic?',-1),(113061,39,25415,25444,'00:17:38.984','00:17:40.193','BODINE: Okay, here we go.',-1),(113062,39,25449,25523,'00:17:40.402','00:17:43.488','She hits the berg on\nthe starboard side, right?',-1),(113063,39,25525,25549,'00:17:43.572','00:17:44.573','She kind of bumps along...',-1),(113064,39,25551,25581,'00:17:44.656','00:17:45.907','...punching holes like\nmorse code...',-1),(113065,39,25587,25618,'00:17:46.157','00:17:47.450','...dit-dit-dit...\nalong the side...',-1),(113066,39,25620,25644,'00:17:47.534','00:17:48.535','...below the water line.',-1),(113067,39,25646,25734,'00:17:48.618','00:17:52.289','Then the forward compartments\nstart to flood.',-1),(113068,39,25740,25767,'00:17:52.539','00:17:53.665','Now, as the water level rises...',-1),(113069,39,25770,25816,'00:17:53.790','00:17:55.667','...it spills over the\nwatertight bulkheads...',-1),(113070,39,25821,25885,'00:17:55.875','00:17:58.545','...which, unfortunately, don\'t\ngo any higher than E deck.',-1),(113071,39,25889,25929,'00:17:58.712','00:18:00.380','So now as the bow goes down...',-1),(113072,39,25935,25995,'00:18:00.630','00:18:03.133','...the stern rises up,\nslow at first...',-1),(113073,39,25997,26035,'00:18:03.216','00:18:04.801','...then faster and faster...',-1),(113074,39,26043,26095,'00:18:05.135','00:18:07.304','...until finally, <i>she\'s</i> got her\nwhole ass sticking up in the air-',-1),(113075,39,26119,26144,'00:18:08.305','00:18:09.347','And that\'s a big ass.',-1),(113076,39,26164,26215,'00:18:10.181','00:18:12.309','We\'re talking\n20, 30,000 tons. Okay?',-1),(113077,39,26221,26271,'00:18:12.559','00:18:14.644','And the hull\'s not designed\nto deal with that pressure.',-1),(113078,39,26273,26314,'00:18:14.728','00:18:16.438','So, what happens?',-1),(113079,39,26325,26366,'00:18:16.896','00:18:18.607','(CLICKING TONGUE) She splits,\nright down to the keel.',-1),(113080,39,26368,26392,'00:18:18.690','00:18:19.691','And the stern...',-1),(113081,39,26403,26427,'00:18:20.150','00:18:21.151','...falls back level.',-1),(113082,39,26429,26453,'00:18:21.234','00:18:22.235','Then...',-1),(113083,39,26455,26479,'00:18:22.319','00:18:23.320','...as the bow sinks...',-1),(113084,39,26481,26527,'00:18:23.403','00:18:25.322','...it pulls the\nstern vertical...',-1),(113085,39,26529,26581,'00:18:25.405','00:18:27.574','...and then finally detaches.',-1),(113086,39,26587,26634,'00:18:27.824','00:18:29.784','Now the stern section\njust kind of bobs there',-1),(113087,39,26636,26679,'00:18:29.868','00:18:31.661','like a cork for\na couple of minutes...',-1),(113088,39,26685,26761,'00:18:31.911','00:18:35.081','...floods, and finally goes\nunder about 2:20 AM...',-1),(113089,39,26767,26820,'00:18:35.332','00:18:37.500','...2 hours and 40 minutes\nafter the collision.',-1),(113090,39,26856,26888,'00:18:39.002','00:18:40.337','The bow section planes away...',-1),(113091,39,26895,26959,'00:18:40.629','00:18:43.298','...landing about a\nhalf a mile away...',-1),(113092,39,26967,27009,'00:18:43.632','00:18:45.383','...going 20, 30 knots when\nit hits the ocean floor.',-1),(113093,39,27017,27054,'00:18:45.717','00:18:47.260','(IMITATES EXPLOSIONS)',-1),(113094,39,27112,27150,'00:18:49.679','00:18:51.264','Pretty cool, huh?',-1),(113095,39,27156,27260,'00:18:51.514','00:18:55.852','Thank you for that fine\nforensic analysis, Mr. Bodine.',-1),(113096,39,27280,27360,'00:18:56.686','00:19:00.023','Of course, the\nexperience of it was...',-1),(113097,39,27380,27420,'00:19:00.857','00:19:02.525','...somewhat different.',-1),(113098,39,27432,27480,'00:19:03.026','00:19:05.028','Will you share it with us?',-1),(113099,39,27557,27598,'00:19:08.239','00:19:09.949','(MUFFLED RADIO CHATTER)',-1),(113100,39,27635,27674,'00:19:11.493','00:19:13.119','(SONAR ECHOING)',-1),(113101,39,28470,28507,'00:19:46.277','00:19:47.821','(BAND PLAYING WALTZ)',-1),(113102,39,28641,28670,'00:19:53.410','00:19:54.619','(SIGHS)',-1),(113103,39,28727,28765,'00:19:56.996','00:19:58.581','Oh. (SOBBING)',-1),(113104,39,28798,28824,'00:19:59.958','00:20:01.000','I\'m taking her to rest.',-1),(113105,39,28826,28850,'00:20:01.084','00:20:02.085','No.',-1),(113106,39,28852,28882,'00:20:02.168','00:20:03.420','Come on, Nana.',-1),(113107,39,28884,28916,'00:20:03.503','00:20:04.838','No!',-1),(113108,39,29014,29054,'00:20:08.925','00:20:10.593','Give me the tape recorder.',-1),(113109,39,29126,29154,'00:20:13.596','00:20:14.764','Tell us, Rose.',-1),(113110,39,29202,29254,'00:20:16.766','00:20:18.935','It\'s been 84 years...',-1),(113111,39,29274,29305,'00:20:19.769','00:20:21.062','It\'s okay. Just try\nto remember anything...',-1),(113112,39,29309,29343,'00:20:21.229','00:20:22.647','...anything at all.',-1),(113113,39,29370,29438,'00:20:23.773','00:20:26.609','<i>Do you want to hear this\nor not, Mr. Lovett?</i>',-1),(113114,39,29534,29606,'00:20:30.613','00:20:33.616','It\'s been 84 years...',-1),(113115,39,29650,29722,'00:20:35.452','00:20:38.455','...and I can still smell\nthe fresh paint.',-1),(113116,39,29765,29834,'00:20:40.248','00:20:43.084','The china had never been used.',-1),(113117,39,29851,29915,'00:20:43.793','00:20:46.463','The sheets had\nnever been slept in.',-1),(113118,39,29955,30049,'00:20:48.131','00:20:52.051','Titanic was called\nthe ship of dreams.',-1),(113119,39,30085,30113,'00:20:53.553','00:20:54.721','And it was.',-1),(113120,39,30143,30184,'00:20:55.972','00:20:57.682','It really was.',-1),(113121,39,30325,30365,'00:21:03.563','00:21:05.231','(CREWMEN SHOUTING)',-1),(113122,39,30395,30431,'00:21:06.483','00:21:07.984','(GULLS CRYING)',-1),(113123,39,30913,30946,'00:21:28.046','00:21:29.422','PORTER: All third-class\npassengers...',-1),(113124,39,30965,30999,'00:21:30.215','00:21:31.633','...with a forward berth...',-1),(113125,39,31002,31057,'00:21:31.758','00:21:34.052','...this way please!\nThis queue!',-1),(113126,39,31070,31106,'00:21:34.594','00:21:36.095','It\'s a big boat, huh?',-1),(113127,39,31112,31159,'00:21:36.346','00:21:38.306','Daddy, it\'s a ship.',-1),(113128,39,31162,31186,'00:21:38.431','00:21:39.432','You\'re right.',-1),(113129,39,31188,31221,'00:21:39.516','00:21:40.892','(CAR HORN HONKING)',-1),(113130,39,31907,31954,'00:22:09.462','00:22:11.422','ROSE: I don\'t see what all\nthe fuss is about.',-1),(113131,39,31969,32017,'00:22:12.048','00:22:14.050','It doesn\'t look any bigger\nthan the Mauretania.',-1),(113132,39,32023,32063,'00:22:14.300','00:22:15.969','CAL: You can be blas\nabout some things, Rose...',-1),(113133,39,32067,32109,'00:22:16.135','00:22:17.887','...but not about Titanic.',-1),(11313